awareness of Christ, with particular reference to the question of Christ's knowledge of himself as both human and divine. This book is a foundational text in critical areas of contemporary theology; however, it was never widely circulated and has remained effectively unknown to contemporary scholars. With this translation the work will finally be made accessible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aElectronic books. -- local. 0aHypostatic union. 0aJesus Christ -- Natures. 0aJesus Christ -- Psychology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh1 aCrowe, Frederick E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrowe, S.J., Frederick, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDoran, S.J., Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShields, Michael G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShields, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311049095440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268195840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442681958423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781442681958/original  a978-3-11-049095-4  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK